<package name="monitoring-plugins-count_file" project="openSUSE:Factory">
  <title>Counts the number of files in a directory</title>
  <description>Use this plugin to count the number of files in a directory and 
issue a warning or critical state if the number exceeds a limit.

Useful if you want to monitor for example:
* a directory which contains error files and must stay empty
* a tmp dir which have to stay under a practical limit

Usage: &lt;filename&gt; &lt;Critical number of files&gt; &lt;Warning number of files&gt;

Examples: count_file.pl 1 10
Examples: count_file.pl 3:10 1:3

</description>
  <devel project="server:monitoring" package="monitoring-plugins-count_file" />
  <url>https://www.monitoringexchange.org/inventory/Check-Plugins/Operating-Systems/Linux/count_file</url>
</package>
